      <div type="commentary" xml:lang="eng">
	<p><ref target="bibl:Sarma1993">Sarma and Varaprasada Rao 1993</ref> reproduce the text and notes of <ref target="bibl:NagarajaRao1985">Nagaraja Rao 1985</ref>, with some typographic errors, but then add a slightly different translation. This edition and translation is based on the plate provided by <ref target="bibl:Sarma1993">Sarma and Varaprasada Rao 1993</ref>.</p>
	<p>This is one of the few inscriptions from Sannati to use the invocatory phrase <foreign xml:lang="pra-Latn">sidham</foreign>.</p>
	<p>For <foreign xml:lang="pra-Latn">putana</foreign> read <foreign xml:lang="pra-Latn">putena</foreign>.</p>
	<p>I suggest that we read <foreign xml:lang="pra-Latn">dovachadako</foreign>, in the meaning of <foreign xml:lang="san-Latn">dvi-upacchadaka</foreign>, a “double covering” or “double awning.”</p>
      </div>
      <div type="edition" xml:lang="pra-Latn">
	<ab>
	  <lb n="1"/>
	  sidham <persName key="pers:Sa-Serāma">serāmasa</persName> pu<app><lem source="#NagarajaRao1985">ta</lem><rdg source="#Sarma1993">tā</rdg></app><app><lem resp="#AO">na</lem><rdg source="#Sarma1993">naṃ</rdg><rdg source="#NagarajaRao1985">ṇaṃ</rdg></app>
	  <lb n="2"/>
	  <persName key="pers:Sa-Muka">mukena</persName>
	  kārito dovachada<app><lem source="#NagarajaRao1985">ko</lem><rdg source="#Sarma1993">ke</rdg></app>
	</ab>
      </div>
      <div type="translation">
	<p>Success. This double awning was caused to be made
	   by <persName key="pers:Sa-Muka">Muka</persName>,
	   the son of <persName key="pers:Sa-Serāma">Serāma</persName>.</p>
      </div>
    </body>
